00:41:11,636 --> 00:41:14,676
Rules designed to make it impossible
for women to enter this world.

498
00:41:15,206 --> 00:41:17,196
But still I'm here. How did this happen?

499
00:41:17,575 --> 00:41:19,855
Because, well, because you...

500
00:41:20,278 --> 00:41:22,147
Because I am the toughest cook
in this kitchen.

501
00:41:22,513 --> 00:41:23,973
I've worked too hard
for too long to get here

502
00:41:24,282 --> 00:41:26,862
and lam not going to jeopardize it
for some garbage boy who got lucky.

503
00:41:27,318 --> 00:41:28,368
Got it?

504
00:41:32,256 --> 00:41:33,106
Wow!

505
00:41:34,025 --> 00:41:37,625
Easy to cook. Easy to eat.
Gusteau makes Chinese food

506
00:41:38,229 --> 00:41:40,218
Chine-easy.

507
00:41:41,733 --> 00:41:45,483
-Excellent work, Francois, as usual.
-It's good, isn't it?

508
00:41:46,104 --> 00:41:49,823
I want you to work up something
for my latest frozen food concept.

509
00:41:50,441 --> 00:41:52,401
Gusteau's Corn Puppies.

510
00:41:52,777 --> 00:41:56,787
They're like corn dogs, only smaller.
Bite size.

511
00:41:57,448 --> 00:41:58,468
What are corn dogs?

512
00:41:58,716 --> 00:41:58,881
Cheap sausages dipped in batter
and deep fried. You know, American.

513
00:41:58,883 --> 00:42:02,633
Cheap sausages dipped in batter
and deep fried. You know, American.

514
00:42:03,454 --> 00:42:04,444
Whip something up.

515
00:42:04,689 --> 00:42:07,788
Maybe Gusteau in overalls
and Huckleberry Tom hat.

516
00:42:08,326 --> 00:42:11,136
Or as a big ear of corn
in doggie make-up.

517
00:42:11,629 --> 00:42:15,169
Yes. But, please, with dignity.

518
00:42:42,126 --> 00:42:43,206
Get my lawyer!

519
00:42:44,262 --> 00:42:46,102
Well, the will stipulates

520
00:42:46,464 --> 00:42:49,774
that if after a period of two years
from the date of death

521
00:42:50,334 --> 00:42:51,473
no heir appears,

522
00:42:51,736 --> 00:42:55,516
Gusteau's business interests
will pass to his sous chef. You.

523
00:42:56,140 --> 00:42:57,890
I know what the will stipulates.

524
00:42:58,242 --> 00:43:02,872
What I want to know is if this letter...
If this boy changes anything!

525
00:43:07,819 --> 00:43:09,459
There's not much resemblance.

526
00:43:09,787 --> 00:43:12,886
There's no resemblance at all.
He is not Gusteau's son.

527
00:43:13,424 --> 00:43:16,204
Gusteau had no children,
and what of the timing of all this?

528
00:43:16,694 --> 00:43:19,564
The deadline in the will
expires in less than a month!

529
00:43:20,131 --> 00:43:21,971
Suddenly,
some boy arrives with a letter

530
00:43:22,333 --> 00:43:26,693
from his recently deceased mother
claiming Gusteau is his father?

531
00:43:27,405 --> 00:43:28,695
Highly suspect!

532
00:43:28,973 --> 00:43:30,613
-This is Gusteau's?
-Yes, yes, yes.

533
00:43:30,942 --> 00:43:32,342
-May I?
-Of course.

534
00:43:32,643 --> 00:43:33,933
But the boy does not know.

535
00:43:34,212 --> 00:43:38,022
She claims she never told him,
or Gusteau, and asks that I not tell.

536
00:43:38,649 --> 00:43:42,159
-Why you? What does she want?
-A job for the boy.

537
00:43:42,753 --> 00:43:45,303
-Only a job?
-Well, yes.

538
00:43:45,756 --> 00:43:47,946
Then what are you worried about?
If he works here,

539
00:43:48,359 --> 00:43:50,969
you'll be able to keep an eye on him
while I do a little digging.

540
00:43:51,429 --> 00:43:53,039
Find out how much of this is real.

541
00:43:53,364 --> 00:43:55,614
I will need you
to collect some DNA samples

542
00:43:56,033 --> 00:43:57,553
from the boy. Hair, maybe.

543
00:43:57,869 --> 00:44:01,619
Mark my words.
The whole thing is highly suspect.

544
00:44:02,940 --> 00:44:04,870
He knows something.

545
00:44:05,243 --> 00:44:08,873
Relax, he's a garbage boy.
l think you can handle him.

546
00:44:15,720 --> 00:44:16,709
What are you doing?

547
00:44:16,954 --> 00:44:18,684
I'm cutting vegetables.
I'm cutting vegetables?

548
00:44:19,023 --> 00:44:20,543
No! You waste energy and time!

549
00:44:20,858 --> 00:44:23,488
You think cooking is a cute job,
like Mommy in the kitchen?

550
00:44:23,961 --> 00:44:25,040
Well, Mommy never had to face

551
00:44:25,296 --> 00:44:26,606
the dinner rush when the orders
come flooding in,

552
00:44:26,898 --> 00:44:28,238
and every dish is different
and none are simple,

553
00:44:28,533 --> 00:44:29,643
and all of the different cooking times,

554
00:44:29,901 --> 00:44:31,011
but must arrive on the customer's table

555
00:44:31,269 --> 00:44:33,049
at exactly the same time,
hot and perfect!

556
00:44:33,404 --> 00:44:35,744
Every second counts,
and you cannot be Mommy!

557
00:44:38,709 --> 00:44:41,459
What is this? Keep your station clear!

558
00:44:41,946 --> 00:44:43,435
When the meal rush comes,
what will happen?

559
00:44:43,748 --> 00:44:45,118
Messy stations slow things down.

560
00:44:45,416 --> 00:44:47,436
Food doesn't go, orders pile up.
Disaster.

561
00:44:47,818 --> 00:44:49,308
I'll make this easy to remember.

562
00:44:49,620 --> 00:44:52,690
Keep your station clear,
or I will kill you!

563
00:44:55,193 --> 00:44:57,183
Your sleeves look like
you threw up on them.

564
00:44:57,562 --> 00:44:59,932
Keep your hands and arms in,
close to the body. Like this. See?

565
00:45:00,364 --> 00:45:01,354
Always return to this position.

566
00:45:01,599 --> 00:45:04,759
Cooks move fast. Sharp utensils,
hot metal, keep your arms in.

567
00:45:05,303 --> 00:45:07,853
You will minimize cuts and burns
and keep your sleeves clean.

568
00:45:08,306 --> 00:45:10,586
Mark of a chef:
Messy apron, clean sleeves.

569
00:45:11,008 --> 00:45:12,528
I know the Gusteau style cold.

570
00:45:12,843 --> 00:45:15,743
In every dish, Chef Gusteau
always has something unexpected.

571
00:45:16,247 --> 00:45:18,797
I will show you.
I memorize all his recipe.

572
00:45:19,250 --> 00:45:22,590
-Always do something unexpected.
-No. Follow the recipe.

573
00:45:23,154 --> 00:45:24,444
-But you just said that...
-No, no, no.

574
00:45:24,722 --> 00:45:27,622
It was his job to be unexpected.
It is our job to...

575
00:45:28,159 --> 00:45:29,859
-Follow his recipes.
-Follow the recipe.

576
00:45:30,194 --> 00:45:32,244
How do you tell how good bread is
without tasting it?

577
00:45:32,630 --> 00:45:36,320
Not the smell, not the look,
but the sound of the crust.

578
00:45:36,934 --> 00:45:37,784
Listen.

579
00:45:39,337 --> 00:45:42,437
Symphony of crackle.
Only great bread sound this way.

580
00:45:43,241 --> 00:45:45,791
The only way to get the best produce
is to have first pick of the day

581
00:45:46,244 --> 00:45:47,944
and there are only two way
to get first pick.

582
00:45:48,279 --> 00:45:51,619
Grow it yourself, or bribe a grower.

583
00:45:52,483 --> 00:45:54,653
Voila! The best restaurant get first pick.

584
00:45:55,052 --> 00:45:58,562
People think haute cuisine is snooty.
So chef must also be snooty.

585
00:45:59,156 --> 00:46:02,556
But not so.
Lalo there ran away from home at 12.

586
00:46:03,127 --> 00:46:05,377
Got hired by circus people
as an acrobat.

587
00:46:05,796 --> 00:46:09,576
And then he get fired for messing
around with the ringmaster's daughter.

588
00:46:10,234 --> 00:46:12,754
-Horst has done time.
-What for?

589
00:46:13,204 --> 00:46:16,164
No one know for sure. He changes
the story every time you ask him.

590
00:46:16,674 --> 00:46:18,374
defrauded a major corporation.

591
00:46:18,709 --> 00:46:21,779
l robbed the second largest bank
in France using only a ballpoint pen.

592
00:46:22,313 --> 00:46:24,533
Il created a hole in the ozone
over Avignon.

593
00:46:24,949 --> 00:46:27,319
I killed a man with this thumb.

594
00:46:27,918 --> 00:46:29,618
Don't ever play cards with Pompidou.

595
00:46:29,954 --> 00:46:33,084
He's been banned from Las Vegas
and Monte Carlo.

596
00:46:33,924 --> 00:46:36,734
-Larousse ran gun for the Resistance.
-Which resistance?

597
00:46:37,228 --> 00:46:39,838
He won't say.
Apparently, they didn't win.

598
00:46:40,598 --> 00:46:41,648
So you see.

599
00:46:41,899 --> 00:46:45,709
We are artist, pirate.
More than cooks are we.

600
00:46:46,337 --> 00:46:49,327
-We?
-Oui. You are one of us now, oui?

601
00:46:50,107 --> 00:46:54,057
Oui. Thank you, by the way,
for all the advice about cooking.

602
00:46:54,945 --> 00:46:57,115
