01:29:02,537 --> 01:29:04,317
Don't! Stop! They'll see you. Stop.

1212
01:29:04,673 --> 01:29:08,675
We're not talking about me.
We're talking about what to do right...

1213
01:29:08,677 --> 01:29:08,727
We're not talking about me.
We're talking about what to do right...

1214
01:29:09,110 --> 01:29:09,960
Rats!

1215
01:29:11,847 --> 01:29:13,217
-Remy!
-Get my knife.

1216
01:29:13,882 --> 01:29:15,312
Don't touch him!

1217
01:29:17,819 --> 01:29:19,899
Thanks for coming back, Little Chef.

1218
01:29:21,489 --> 01:29:23,509
I know this sounds insane, but...

1219
01:29:23,892 --> 01:29:26,142
Well,
the truth sounds insane sometimes.

1220
01:29:26,561 --> 01:29:30,130
But that doesn't mean it's not the truth.

1221
01:29:31,366 --> 01:29:35,086
And the truth is, I have no talent at all.

1222
01:29:36,371 --> 01:29:39,801
But this rat,
he's the one behind these recipes.

1223
01:29:40,375 --> 01:29:44,855
He's the cook. The real cook.
He's been hiding under my toque.

1224
01:29:45,814 --> 01:29:48,064
He's been controlling my actions.

1225
01:29:49,818 --> 01:29:52,948
He's the reason I can cook the food
that's exciting everyone.

1226
01:29:53,588 --> 01:29:56,308
The reason Ego is outside that door.

1227
01:29:56,925 --> 01:29:59,385
You've been giving me credit
for his gift.

1228
01:29:59,995 --> 01:30:01,394
I know it's hard to believe.

1229
01:30:01,696 --> 01:30:04,306
But, hey, you believed I could cook,
right?

1230
01:30:06,401 --> 01:30:10,061
Look, this works.
It's crazy, but it works.

1231
01:30:11,039 --> 01:30:13,209
We can be
the greatest restaurant in Paris,

1232
01:30:13,608 --> 01:30:18,388
and this rat, this brilliant Little Chef,
can lead us there.

1233
01:30:19,781 --> 01:30:21,891
What do you say? You with me?

1234
01:32:10,158 --> 01:32:11,008
Dad.

1235
01:32:15,230 --> 01:32:17,839
Dad, I don't know what to say.

1236
01:32:18,400 --> 01:32:21,940
Il was wrong about your friend
and about you.

1237
01:32:22,837 --> 01:32:26,237
I don't want you to think
I'm choosing this over family.

1238
01:32:26,908 --> 01:32:29,338
I can't choose
between two halves of myself.

1239
01:32:29,778 --> 01:32:33,148
I'm not talking about cooking.
I'm talking about guts.

1240
01:32:34,315 --> 01:32:36,424
This really means that much to you?

1241
01:32:44,726 --> 01:32:47,335
We're not cooks, but we are family.

1242
01:32:47,896 --> 01:32:50,526
You tell us what to do,
and we'll get it done.

1243
01:32:54,836 --> 01:32:55,686
City of Paris - Ministry of Public Health
Health Inspector Dist. 5

1244
01:32:58,873 --> 01:33:02,062
-Stop that health inspector.
-Delta Team, go, go, go, go!

1245
01:33:02,710 --> 01:33:04,580
The rest of you stay and help Remy.

1246
01:33:21,496 --> 01:33:22,546
EMPLOYEES
MUST WASH HANDS!

1247
01:33:27,969 --> 01:33:29,803
Team three will be handling fish.
Team four, roasted items.

1248
01:33:29,804 --> 01:33:31,234
Team three will be handling fish.
Team four, roasted items.

1249
01:33:31,639 --> 01:33:36,419
Team five, grill. Team six, sauces.
Get to your stations. Let's go, go, go!

1250
01:33:37,378 --> 01:33:39,567
Those handling food
will walk on two legs.

1251
01:33:49,591 --> 01:33:51,321
We need someone to wait tables.

1252
01:34:06,841 --> 01:34:09,501
I'm sorry for any delay,
but we're a little short tonight.

1253
01:34:09,978 --> 01:34:11,968
Please, take all of the time you need.

1254
01:34:15,416 --> 01:34:17,696
He came in late one more time
and all of a sudden he...

1255
01:34:22,323 --> 01:34:24,373
Make sure that steak
is nice and tenderized.

1256
01:34:24,759 --> 01:34:26,809
Work it. Stick and move.
Stick and move.

1257
01:34:27,195 --> 01:34:30,295
Easy with that sole meuniére.
Less salt. More butter.

1258
01:34:30,932 --> 01:34:32,602
Only use the mimolette cheese.

1259
01:34:32,967 --> 01:34:36,156
Whoa! Compose the salad
like you were painting a picture.

1260
01:34:36,804 --> 01:34:39,114
Not too much vinaigrette
on that salade composée.

1261
01:34:39,541 --> 01:34:42,261
Don't let that beurre blanc separate.
Keep whisking.

1262
01:34:42,810 --> 01:34:46,470
Gently poach the scallops.
Taste check. Spoons down.

1263
01:34:47,182 --> 01:34:49,232
Good. Too much salt. Good.

1264
01:34:49,717 --> 01:34:52,267
Don't boil the consommé,
it'll toughen the pheasant. Emile!

1265
01:34:52,720 --> 01:34:53,680
Sorry.

1266
01:34:57,425 --> 01:34:59,325
Colette, wait! Colette.

1267
01:35:00,028 --> 01:35:03,568
-You came back. Colette...
-Don't say a word.

1268
01:35:04,165 --> 01:35:05,535
If l think about it,
I might change my mind.

1269
01:35:05,833 --> 01:35:08,003
Just tell me what the rat wants to cook.

1270
01:35:11,406 --> 01:35:13,596
Ratatouille? It's a peasant dish.

1271
01:35:14,042 --> 01:35:16,652
Are you sure
you want to serve this to Ego?

1272
01:35:35,496 --> 01:35:39,476
What? I am making ratatouille.
Well, how would you prepare it?

1273
01:36:13,034 --> 01:36:15,813
Ratatouille? They must be joking.

1274
01:37:07,088 --> 01:37:08,638
No, it can't be.

1275
01:37:09,457 --> 01:37:12,647
Who cooked the ratatouille?
I demand to know!

1276
01:37:20,101 --> 01:37:21,531
I can't remember the last time

1277
01:37:21,836 --> 01:37:24,736
l asked a waiter
to give my compliments to the chef.

1278
01:37:26,107 --> 01:37:28,567
And now I find myself
in the extraordinary position

1279
01:37:29,010 --> 01:37:30,850
of having my waiter be the chef.

1280
01:37:31,312 --> 01:37:33,892
Thanks, but I'm just your waiter tonight.

1281
01:37:35,316 --> 01:37:37,486
Then who do I thank for the meal?

1282
01:37:38,653 --> 01:37:40,143
Excuse me a minute.

1283
01:37:51,366 --> 01:37:52,236
You must be the chef.

1284
01:37:52,467 --> 01:37:56,246
If you wish to meet the chef, you must
wait until all other customer have gone.

1285
01:37:58,806 --> 01:37:59,826
So be it.

1286
01:38:21,662 --> 01:38:23,882
At first, Ego thinks it's a joke.

1287
01:38:24,399 --> 01:38:29,619
But as Linguini explains,
Ego's smile disappears.

1288
01:38:35,943 --> 01:38:39,513
He doesn't react
beyond asking an occasional question.

1289
01:38:40,548 --> 01:38:44,388
And when the story is done,
Ego stands, thanks us for the meal...

1290
01:38:45,019 --> 01:38:46,479
Thank you for the meal.

1291
01:38:46,788 --> 01:38:49,308
..and leaves without another word.

1292
01:38:51,926 --> 01:38:55,386
The following day his review appears.

1293
01:38:58,399 --> 01:39:01,999
In many ways,
the work of a critic is easy.

1294
01:39:02,703 --> 01:39:06,423
We risk very little,
yet enjoy a position over those

1295
01:39:07,041 --> 01:39:10,611
who offer up their work
and their selves to our judgment.

1296
01:39:11,345 --> 01:39:16,065
We thrive on negative criticism,
which is fun to write and to read.

1297
01:39:17,251 --> 01:39:22,991
But the bitter truth we critics must face
is that in the grand scheme of things,

1298
01:39:23,891 --> 01:39:27,401
the average piece of junk
is probably more meaningful

1299
01:39:27,995 --> 01:39:30,865
than our criticism designating it so.

1300
01:39:31,632 --> 01:39:35,262
But there are times
when a critic truly risks something

1301
01:39:35,870 --> 01:39:39,650
and that is in the discovery
and defense of the new.

1302
01:39:40,274 --> 01:39:44,314
The world is often unkind
to new talent, new creations.

1303
01:39:45,079 --> 01:39:47,249
The new needs friends.

1304
01:39:47,849 --> 01:39:50,949
Last night,
! experienced something new,

1305
01:39:51,586 --> 01:39:55,946
an extraordinary meal
from a singularly unexpected source.

1306
01:39:56,757 --> 01:39:59,067
To say that both the meal
and its maker

1307
01:39:59,494 --> 01:40:02,563
have challenged my preconceptions
about fine cooking

1308
01:40:03,097 --> 01:40:05,467
is a gross understatement.

1309
01:40:06,200 --> 01:40:09,010
They have rocked me to my core.

1310
01:40:10,137 --> 01:40:13,177
In the past, 1 have made no secret
of my disdain

1311
01:40:13,708 --> 01:40:18,067
for Chef Gusteau's famous motto,
"Anyone can cook."

1312
01:40:18,980 --> 01:40:24,429
But I realize only now
do truly understand what he meant.

1313
01:40:25,486 --> 01:40:28,946
Not everyone
can become a great artist,

1314
01:40:29,524 --> 01:40:33,334
but a great artist
can come from anywhere.

1315
01:40:34,462 --> 01:40:37,332
It is difficult to imagine
more humble origins

1316
01:40:37,832 --> 01:40:41,232
than those of the genius
now cooking at Gusteau's,

1317
01:40:41,802 --> 01:40:44,291
who is, in this critic's opinion,

1318
01:40:44,739 --> 01:40:48,459
nothing less
than the finest chef in France.

1319
01:40:49,176 --> 01:40:51,044
! will be returning to Gusteau's soon,
hungry for more.

1320
01:40:51,045 --> 01:40:54,085
! will be returning to Gusteau's soon,
hungry for more.

1321
01:40:54,882 --> 01:40:57,751
It was a great night.
The happiest of my life.

1322
01:40:58,352 --> 01:40:59,586
But the only thing predictable
about life is its unpredictability.

1323
01:40:59,587 --> 01:41:00,887
CLOSED

1324
01:41:00,888 --> 01:41:01,708
CLOSED

1325
01:41:01,923 --> 01:41:03,032
FOR VIOLATION OF FRENCH
HEALTH AND SAFETY CODES

1326
01:41:03,291 --> 01:41:05,781
Well, we had to let Skinner
and the health inspector loose,

1327
01:41:06,260 --> 01:41:08,370
and of course they ratted us out.

1328
01:41:09,030 --> 01:41:10,460
The food didn't matter.

1329
01:41:10,765 --> 01:41:12,845
Once it got out
there were rats in the kitchen,

1330
01:41:13,234 --> 01:41:15,044
oh, man, the restaurant was closed.

1331
01:41:15,403 --> 01:41:17,803
Ego lost his job and his credibility.

1332
01:41:18,239 --> 01:41:19,938
But don't feel too bad for him.

1333
01:41:20,274 --> 01:41:23,344
He's doing very well
as a small business investor.

1334
01:41:24,111 --> 01:41:26,361
-He seems very happy.
-How do you know?

1335
01:41:34,855 --> 01:41:36,724
Got to go. Dinner rush.

1336
01:41:44,565 --> 01:41:46,025
You know how he likes it.

1337
01:41:51,606 --> 01:41:53,005
Thanks, Little Chef.

1338
01:41:59,880 --> 01:42:02,370
Can I interest you
in a dessert this evening?

1339
01:42:02,817 --> 01:42:05,567
-Don't you always?
-Which one would you like?

1340
01:42:07,088 --> 01:42:08,697
Surprise me.

1341
01:42:14,328 --> 01:42:17,348
Can I interest you
in a dessert this evening?

1342
01:42:21,235 --> 01:42:24,455
Hey, believe me, that story
gets better when I tell it, okay?

1343
01:42:26,807 --> 01:42:29,527
Come on. Bring some food over here,
we're starving!

